column5: Went out to Cooks this evening and had some more non stop action. The body count was 14-15 pike, 8-9 LMB's including a 5lber, 4 Bowfin, and a bunch of panfish. Once again, everything was caught on Northam Spinnerbaits.
Another bow fin .Man it takes me a week to catch that many fish  MTP

I had no idea that bowfin put up such a nice fight, but man are they ugly. Good thing I got  lip grip.  I know the figures sound inflated, but it was one of those rare occasions where it wasn't called fishing, it was called catching.  Cheers!
Nice fish. That dogfish is huge.
WTG, man I can't wait to get back out there.
very nice looking fish, looks like a fun outing. Thanks for sharing.
Sounds like a great night.  Nice mix for a single lure - gotta love spinnerbaits.
